'''buckram'''
# A coarse cloth of linen or hemp, stiffened with size or glue, used in garments to keep them in the form intended, and for wrappers to cover merchandise.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1882''': Buckram was probably from the first a stiffened material employed for lining, often dyed. &mdash; James Edwin Thorold Rogers, ''A History of Agriculture and Prices in England'', Volume 4, p. 557.
